Open Source License

NanaDraw is licensed under a modified version of the Apache License 2.0, with the following additional conditions:

NanaDraw may be used commercially. However, if any of the following conditions is met, a commercial license must be obtained from the developers of NanaDraw:

a. Commercial scale threshold:
   Monthly active users (MAU) exceed 100 million; or
   Monthly revenue exceeds USD 20 million.
   The above thresholds shall be calculated on a consolidated basis across you and your Affiliates.

b. Online service attribution requirement:
   If you provide online services to third parties based on NanaDraw, you must clearly indicate in a prominent place in the relevant product or service that NanaDraw is used.

If any of the above conditions is violated, this license will terminate automatically.

